   ],
   "source": [
    "viz = Vizier(columns=[\"*\", \"_RAJ2000\", \"_DEJ2000\"])\n",
    "viz.ROW_LIMIT = -1  # sets the limit to infinity\n",
    "table = viz.get_catalogs(\"I/293/npm2cros\")[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(table)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's create a MOC from the coordinates of this table"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "moc = MOC.from_lonlat(\n",
    "    table[\"_RAJ2000\"].T * u.deg,\n",
    "    table[\"_DEJ2000\"].T * u.deg,\n",
    "    max_norder=6,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 4000x2000 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(dpi=400, figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "with WCS(\n",
    "    fig,\n",
    "    fov=160 * u.deg,\n",
    "    center=SkyCoord(0, 0, unit=\"deg\", frame=\"galactic\"),\n",
    "    coordsys=\"galactic\",\n",
    "    rotation=Angle(0, u.degree),\n",
    "    projection=\"AIT\",\n",
    ") as wcs:\n",
    "    ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 1, 1, projection=wcs, frame_class=EllipticalFrame)\n",
    "\n",
    "    moc.fill(\n",
    "        ax=ax,\n",
    "        wcs=wcs,\n",
    "        edgecolor=\"teal\",\n",
    "        facecolor=\"orange\",\n",
    "        linewidth=1.0,\n",
    "        fill=True,\n",
    "        alpha=0.8,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    moc.border(ax=ax, wcs=wcs, color=\"k\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.grid(True)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()"
   ]
  }
